(4. FAILED PAYMENTS) Tj
T*
(=============================================================) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(4.1 Why a Payment Might Fail) Tj
T*
(Common reasons include:) Tj
T*
(- Insufficient funds) Tj
T*
(- Card expired or incorrect expiry date entered) Tj
T*
(- Billing address does not match the card issuer's records) Tj
T*
(- Bank declined the transaction as suspicious \(call your bank to authorize\)) Tj
T*
(- Daily spending limit reached) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(4.2 What Happens When a Payment Fails) Tj
T*
(Your order is not placed. You will see an error message at checkout specifying the) Tj
T*
(reason \(if available from your bank\). No hold or charge is made to your card in the) Tj
T*
(event of a complete failure. However, some banks show a temporary "authorization) Tj
T*
(hold" that typically disappears within 3 to 5 business days.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(4.3 Updating Payment and Retrying) Tj
T*
(If your payment fails, you can:) Tj
T*
(- Correct your card details and retry immediately) Tj
T*
(- Use a different payment method at checkout) Tj
T*
(- Contact your bank to authorize the transaction, then retry) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(=============================================================) Tj
T*
(5. AUTHORIZATION HOLDS) Tj
T*
(=============================================================) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(When you place an order, we place a temporary authorization hold on your card for the) Tj
T*
(full order amount. This hold is not a charge ? it is a reservation of funds. The) Tj
T*
(actual charge posts when your order ships. If your order is cancelled before) Tj
T*
(shipment, the hold is released. Release times vary by bank \(typically 3 to 10) Tj
T*
(business days\).) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(For split-shipment orders, you may see multiple smaller charges as each shipment is) Tj
T*
(dispatched.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(=============================================================) Tj
T*
(6. INVOICES AND RECEIPTS) Tj
T*
(=============================================================) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(6.1 Order Receipts) Tj
T*
(A receipt is automatically emailed to the address on file after each successful) Tj
T*
(payment. Receipts are also available in Account > Order History > View Receipt.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(6.2 VAT and Tax Invoices) Tj
T*
(If you require a formal VAT or tax invoice \(for business expense purposes\), email) Tj
T*
(billing@shopexample.com with your order number and business details \(company name,) Tj
ET
endstream
